head(sales)

sales$DstC<-as.factor(sales$DstC)

library(ggplot2)
ggplot(sales, aes(NoSO, Avg_So))+geom_point()

library(dplyr)
## 
## Attaching package: 'dplyr'
## The following objects are masked from 'package:stats':
## 
##     filter, lag
## The following objects are masked from 'package:base':
## 
##     intersect, setdiff, setequal, union
rescale_sales<- sales %>%
  mutate(Sales=scale(Sales),
         NoSO= scale(NoSO),
         Avg_So=scale(Avg_So))
head(rescale_sales)

Find Optimal k

kmeans_withinss<- function(k){
  cluster<- kmeans(rescale_sales[,5:7], k)
  return(cluster$tot.withinss)
}
kmeans_withinss(2)
## [1] 7634.81
max_k<-10
wss<-sapply(2:max_k,kmeans_withinss )


elbow <-data.frame(2:max_k, wss)

# Plot the graph with gglop
ggplot(elbow, aes(x = X2.max_k, y = wss)) +
    geom_point() +
    geom_line() +
    scale_x_continuous(breaks = seq(1, 10, by = 1))

Examining the clusters

kmeans.sales<-kmeans(rescale_sales[,5:7], 4)
#kmeans.sales$cluster
#kmeans.sales$centers
#kmeans.sales$size


cluster<-as.data.frame(kmeans.sales$cluster)
cluster<-cluster %>% rename(Cluster = 'kmeans.sales$cluster')
sales<- cbind(sales,cluster)
head(sales)
#str(sales)

#sales<-sales[-c(8:8)]

ggplot(sales, aes(NoSO, Avg_So))+
  geom_point(aes(color=factor(Cluster)))+ scale_color_manual(values = c('1'="#00AFBB", '2'="#E7B800", '3'="#FC4E07",'4'="#52854C"))

library(cowplot)
## 
## ********************************************************
## Note: As of version 1.0.0, cowplot does not change the
##   default ggplot2 theme anymore. To recover the previous
##   behavior, execute:
##   theme_set(theme_cowplot())
## ********************************************************
g_count<-ggplot(sales, aes(Cluster))+
  geom_histogram(aes(fill=factor(Cluster)))+
  scale_fill_manual(values = c('1'="#00AFBB", '2'="#E7B800", '3'="#FC4E07",'4'="#52854C"))

g_sales<-ggplot(sales, aes(Cluster, Sales/1000000))+
  geom_col(aes(fill=factor(Cluster)))+labs(y='Sales, in Milions')+ scale_fill_manual(values = c('1'="#00AFBB", '2'="#E7B800", '3'="#FC4E07",'4'="#52854C"))

plot_grid(g_count,g_sales)
## `stat_bin()` using `bins = 30`. Pick better value with `binwidth`.

g_Avg_So<-ggplot(sales, aes(Cluster, Avg_So))+
  geom_boxplot(aes(fill=factor(Cluster)))+ scale_fill_manual(values = c('1'="#00AFBB", '2'="#E7B800", '3'="#FC4E07",'4'="#52854C"))
g_NoSO<-ggplot(sales, aes(Cluster, NoSO))+
  geom_boxplot(aes(fill=factor(Cluster)))+ scale_fill_manual(values = c('1'="#00AFBB", '2'="#E7B800", '3'="#FC4E07",'4'="#52854C"))
g_Sales<-ggplot(sales, aes(Cluster, Sales))+
  geom_boxplot(aes(fill=factor(Cluster)))+ scale_fill_manual(values = c('1'="#00AFBB", '2'="#E7B800", '3'="#FC4E07",'4'="#52854C"))

plot_grid(g_Avg_So,g_NoSO,g_Sales)

Factor in Categories in Analysis

sales_cat<-read.csv("CustomerByCateg.csv")
head(sales_cat)
#any(is.na(sales))
#str(sales)
sales_cat$Category<-as.factor(sales_cat$Category)
sales_cat$CatType <-as.factor(sales_cat$CatType )
sales_cat$SoldTo<-as.factor((sales_cat$SoldTo))
sales_cat$SoldTo_Name<-as.factor((sales_cat$SoldTo_Name))
sales_cat$Customer_Group<-as.factor((sales_cat$Customer_Group))
#sales<-sales[-c(8:8)]
#x$name <- factor(x$name, levels = x$name[order(x$val)])
#sales$Category<-factor(sales$Category, levels = sales$Category[order(sales$Sales)] )
ggplot(sales_cat, aes(Category, Sales))+ geom_col(aes(fill=CatType))+
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90))

a<-ggplot(sales_cat, aes(CatType, Sales/1000000)) + geom_col(aes(fill=Customer_Group))+
  labs(y='Sales')+ scale_fill_manual(values = c('1'="#00AFBB", '2'="#E7B800", '3'="#FC4E07",'4'="#52854C"))
b<-ggplot(sales_cat, aes(Customer_Group, Sales/1000000)) + geom_col(aes(fill=CatType))+
  labs(y='Sales')
plot_grid(a,b)

sales_major<-subset(sales_cat,sales_cat$CatType=='Yes')
ggplot(sales_major, aes(Category, Sales))+
  geom_col(aes(fill=factor(Customer_Group)))+ theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90))+labs(title="Major categories")+
  scale_fill_manual(values = c('1'="#00AFBB", '2'="#E7B800", '3'="#FC4E07",'4'="#52854C"))

sales_minor<-subset(sales_cat,sales_cat$CatType=='No')
ggplot(sales_minor, aes(Category, Sales))+
  geom_col(aes(fill=factor(Customer_Group)))+ theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90))+labs(title="Minor categories")+
  scale_fill_manual(values = c('1'="#00AFBB", '2'="#E7B800", '3'="#FC4E07",'4'="#52854C"))

sales_cat_cl2<-filter(sales_cat, Customer_Group==2,CatType=='Yes')
sales_cat_cl2$Sales[sales_cat_cl2$Sales > 20000] <- median(sales_cat_cl2$Sales)

sales_cat_cl3<-filter(sales_cat, Customer_Group==3,CatType=='Yes')
sales_cat_cl3$Sales[sales_cat_cl3$Sales > 25000] <- median(sales_cat_cl3$Sales)

sales_cat_cl4<-filter(sales_cat, Customer_Group==4,CatType=='Yes')

sales_cat_cl1<-filter(sales_cat, Customer_Group==1,CatType=='Yes')
sales_cat_cl1$Sales[sales_cat_cl1$Sales > 23000 ] <- median(sales_cat_cl1$Sales)
sales_major$Sales[sales_major$Sales > 10000 | sales_major$Sales < -3000] <- median(sales_major$Sales)
ggplot(sales_major, aes(Category, Sales))+geom_boxplot(fill='grey')+
